## Goal
Automatically rebase stack onto latest main when behind.

## Implementation

```typescript
// src/git/rebase.ts

interface RebaseResult {
  success: boolean;
  commitCount: number;
  conflictFile?: string;
}

async function rebaseOntoMain(): Promise<RebaseResult> {
  const defaultBranch = await getDefaultBranch();

  // Count commits in stack
  const mergeBase = await $\`git merge-base HEAD origin/\${defaultBranch}\`.text();
  const commitCount = parseInt(
    await $\`git rev-list \${mergeBase.trim()}..HEAD --count\`.text(), 
    10
  );

  // Attempt rebase
  const result = await $\`git rebase origin/\${defaultBranch}\`.nothrow();

  if (result.exitCode === 0) {
    return { success: true, commitCount };
  }

  // Check for conflict
  const status = await $\`git status --porcelain\`.text();
  const conflictMatch = status.match(/^UU (.+)$/m);

  if (conflictMatch) {
    return { 
      success: false, 
      commitCount, 
      conflictFile: conflictMatch[1] 
    };
  }

  throw new Error('Rebase failed for unknown reason');
}
```

### Preserving Trailers
Git rebase preserves commit messages, so Taspr trailers survive automatically.

## Integration with Sync
```typescript
async function sync() {
  if (await isStackBehindMain()) {
    console.log('Rebasing onto origin/main...');

    const result = await rebaseOntoMain();

    if (result.success) {
      console.log(\`✓ Rebased \${result.commitCount} commit(s)\`);
    } else {
      // Handle conflict...
    }
  }
}
```

