## Goal
Implement precise conflict prediction for the group TUI, warning users when reordering commits would cause merge conflicts.

## Context
This is part of Epic 7: Group Management. When users reorder commits in the TUI, we need to predict whether the reorder would cause a conflict BEFORE they commit to it. This uses a hybrid approach: fast file-level check first, then precise merge simulation if files overlap.

## UX Design
When moving a commit past another that would conflict:

```
» A e5f6a7b8  Add login endpoint       ← MOVING
  A c9d0e1f2  Fix login bug            ✗ CONFLICT (auth.ts:15-22)

─────────────────────────────────────────
✗ Moving past "Fix login bug" will conflict in auth.ts (lines 15-22)
```

Status indicators:
- ✓ clean - no file overlap, safe to move
- ⚠️ warning - file overlap but merge would succeed (same file, different lines)
- ✗ conflict - actual merge conflict detected

## Implementation

### Hybrid Approach
```typescript
interface ConflictResult {
  status: 'clean' | 'warning' | 'conflict';
  files?: string[];           // Overlapping files
  conflictLines?: string[];   // e.g., "auth.ts:15-22"
}
```

### Step 1: Fast File Overlap Check
```typescript
// Get files modified by a commit
async function getCommitFiles(hash: string): Promise<string[]> {
  const result = await $`git diff-tree --no-commit-id --name-only -r ${hash}`.text();
  return result.trim().split('\n').filter(Boolean);
}

// Check if two commits modify overlapping files
async function checkFileOverlap(commitA: string, commitB: string): Promise<string[]> {
  const filesA = await getCommitFiles(commitA);
  const filesB = await getCommitFiles(commitB);
  const setA = new Set(filesA);
  return filesB.filter(f => setA.has(f));
}
```

### Step 2: Precise Merge Simulation (only if files overlap)
```typescript
// Use git merge-tree to simulate actual merge
async function simulateMerge(
  base: string, 
  commitA: string, 
  commitB: string
): Promise<ConflictResult> {
  // git merge-tree simulates merge without touching working tree
  // Exit code 0 with CONFLICT in output = conflicts exist
  const result = await $`git merge-tree ${base} ${commitA} ${commitB}`
    .nothrow()
    .text();

  if (result.includes('CONFLICT')) {
    // Parse conflict details from output
    const conflicts = parseConflictOutput(result);
    return { 
      status: 'conflict', 
      files: conflicts.files,
      conflictLines: conflicts.lines 
    };
  }

  return { status: 'warning', files: overlappingFiles };
}
```

### Caching
Cache file lists during TUI session to avoid repeated git calls:
```typescript
const fileCache = new Map<string, string[]>();

async function getCommitFilesCached(hash: string): Promise<string[]> {
  if (!fileCache.has(hash)) {
    fileCache.set(hash, await getCommitFiles(hash));
  }
  return fileCache.get(hash)!;
}
```

## Git Commands Used
- `git diff-tree --no-commit-id --name-only -r <commit>` - get files modified (fast)
- `git merge-tree <base> <commit1> <commit2>` - simulate merge (precise, non-destructive)

