## Goal
Build a PRUnit[] array from commits, identifying which commits are singles and which belong to groups.

## Background
After parsing commits and their trailers, we need to understand the stack structure:
- Commits without group trailers become individual PRUnits (type: 'single')
- Commits between Taspr-Group-Start and Taspr-Group-End become one PRUnit (type: 'group')

## Data Structures

```typescript
interface PRUnit {
  type: 'single' | 'group';
  id: string;           // Taspr-Commit-Id (single) or group-id (group)
  title: string;        // Commit subject (single) or Taspr-Group-Title (group)
  commitIds: string[];  // All Taspr-Commit-Id values in this unit
  commits: string[];    // Current git hashes
}

interface CommitInfo {
  hash: string;
  subject: string;
  body: string;
  trailers: CommitTrailers;
}
```

## Algorithm

```typescript
function detectPRUnits(commits: CommitInfo[]): PRUnit[] {
  const units: PRUnit[] = [];
  let currentGroup: Partial<PRUnit> | null = null;

  for (const commit of commits) {
    const commitId = commit.trailers['Taspr-Commit-Id'];
    const startId = commit.trailers['Taspr-Group-Start'];
    const endId = commit.trailers['Taspr-Group-End'];

    if (startId && !currentGroup) {
      // Start a new group
      currentGroup = {
        type: 'group',
        id: startId,
        title: commit.trailers['Taspr-Group-Title'] || commit.subject,
        commitIds: [commitId],
        commits: [commit.hash],
      };
    } else if (currentGroup) {
      // Add to current group
      currentGroup.commitIds!.push(commitId);
      currentGroup.commits!.push(commit.hash);

      if (endId === currentGroup.id) {
        // End of group
        units.push(currentGroup as PRUnit);
        currentGroup = null;
      }
    } else {
      // Single commit
      units.push({
        type: 'single',
        id: commitId,
        title: commit.subject,
        commitIds: [commitId],
        commits: [commit.hash],
      });
    }
  }

  // Handle unclosed group (validation error - covered in next task)
  return units;
}
```

## Edge Cases
1. **Empty stack**: Return empty array
2. **All singles**: Each commit becomes a PRUnit
3. **All in one group**: One PRUnit with all commits
4. **Mixed**: Singles and groups interspersed
5. **Commit without Taspr-Commit-Id**: Still include (ID will be undefined, handled by sync later)

