# In-Memory Rebase (Cherry-Pick Sequence)

Implement true rebasing onto a new base using in-memory merge-tree.

## Function

```typescript
interface RebaseResult {
  ok: true;
  newTip: string;
} | {
  ok: false;
  conflictCommit: string;
  conflictInfo: string;
}

async function inMemoryRebase(
  onto: string,
  commits: string[],  // Commits to replay (oldest first)
  options: GitOptions = {}
): Promise<RebaseResult>
```

## Algorithm

```typescript
let currentTip = onto;

for (const commit of commits) {
  const parent = await getParent(commit);  // Original parent

  // Three-way merge: base=original parent, ours=currentTip, theirs=commit
  const mergeResult = await mergeTree(parent, currentTip, commit);

  if (!mergeResult.ok) {
    return { ok: false, conflictCommit: commit, ... };
  }

  const message = await getCommitMessage(commit);
  const env = await getAuthorEnv(commit);  // Author only (committer = now)

  currentTip = await createCommit(mergeResult.tree, [currentTip], message, env);
}

return { ok: true, newTip: currentTip };
```

## Key Points
- Uses `git merge-tree --write-tree` for three-way merge
- Preserves author info, updates committer (standard rebase behavior)
- On conflict: returns immediately, nothing modified
- On success: returns new tip SHA (caller finalizes)

