## Goal
Implement `taspr land --all` to merge all consecutive ready PRs.

## Behavior
Merge PRs from the bottom up, stopping at the first non-ready PR.

```
Stack: [#142 ready] → [#143 ready] → [#144 not ready] → [#145 ready]

taspr land --all merges #142 and #143, then stops at #144.
```

## Implementation

```typescript
async function landAll() {
  const units = await getEnrichedPRUnits();

  let merged = 0;

  for (const unit of units) {
    if (unit.pr?.state !== 'open') continue;

    const status = await getPRMergeStatus(unit.pr.number);

    if (!status.mergeable) {
      if (merged > 0) {
        console.log(\`\\nStopping at PR #\${unit.pr.number} (not ready)\`);
      }
      break;
    }

    console.log(\`Merging PR #\${unit.pr.number} (\${unit.title})...\`);
    await mergePR(unit.pr.number);
    console.log(\`✓ Merged PR #\${unit.pr.number} to main\\n\`);
    merged++;

    // Brief pause for GitHub to update
    await sleep(1000);
  }

  if (merged === 0) {
    console.log('No ready PRs to merge');
  } else {
    console.log(\`\\n✓ Merged \${merged} PR(s)\`);
  }
}
```

