## Goal
Block sync operations when there are uncommitted changes.

## Background
Rebasing with uncommitted changes can cause problems:
- Changes get lost
- Conflicts are harder to resolve
- State becomes confusing

taspr should detect and block this upfront with a clear message.

## Implementation

```typescript
// src/git/status.ts

interface WorkingTreeStatus {
  isDirty: boolean;
  hasUnstagedChanges: boolean;
  hasStagedChanges: boolean;
  hasUntrackedFiles: boolean;
}

async function getWorkingTreeStatus(): Promise<WorkingTreeStatus> {
  // Check for any changes
  const status = await $`git status --porcelain`.text();

  const lines = status.trim().split('\n').filter(Boolean);

  return {
    isDirty: lines.length > 0,
    hasUnstagedChanges: lines.some(l => l[1] !== ' '),
    hasStagedChanges: lines.some(l => l[0] !== ' ' && l[0] !== '?'),
    hasUntrackedFiles: lines.some(l => l.startsWith('??')),
  };
}

async function requireCleanWorkingTree(): Promise<void> {
  const status = await getWorkingTreeStatus();

  if (status.hasStagedChanges || status.hasUnstagedChanges) {
    throw new DirtyWorkingTreeError(status);
  }

  // Note: Untracked files are okay—they don't affect rebase
}
```

