git push --force origin abc123:refs/heads/taspr/msims/a1b2c3d4

# Delete branch
git push origin --delete taspr/msims/a1b2c3d4
```

### Stack Ordering
Push branches bottom-to-top so parent branches exist before creating child PRs:

```typescript
async function pushAllBranches(units: PRUnit[]): Promise<Map<string, string>> {
  const config = await getBranchNameConfig();
  const branches = new Map<string, string>(); // prId -> branchName

  // Push in order (oldest first = bottom of stack)
  for (const unit of units) {
    const branch = await pushPRUnitBranch(unit, config);
    branches.set(unit.id, branch);
  }

  return branches;
}
```

## Edge Cases
1. **Branch already exists**: Push still works (updates branch)
2. **Permission denied**: Clear error about repo access
3. **No remote**: Error about missing origin

